issues.description: ExcellenceLand's constructor in the solution repository declares an extra String parameter ("name") that is not an attribute in the UML/problem statement. The problem explicitly requires a public constructor that takes all attributes from the UML in the same order. The UML lists only excellencyLevel: double, excellentEnough: boolean (and the relation rides: List<Ride>), so the constructor should be (double excellencyLevel, boolean excellentEnough, List<Ride> rides). The extra parameter breaks the stated constructor-contract and will confuse students and/or fail automated checks that expect the constructor parameters to match the UML exactly.
